turns.utterance: A few months ago I graduated from Stanford University! Not to brag, but it's considered one of the most prestigious universities in the world.
It's in Stanford, California. About 20 miles outside of San Jose. I believe it's considered part of Silicon Valley.
turns.response: Oh, so near the tech community. Is it Ivy League?

turns.utterance: No, I don't think so. The eight Ivy League schools are Brown, Columbia, Cornell, Darmouth, Harvard, UPenn, Princeton, and Yale. Stanford is still regarded very highly, though.
turns.response: I wonder what their graduation rate is.

turns.utterance: Yeah, I'm not really sure either. One of the little known things about Stanford is how strong of a fundraising institution they are. I think they're the first school to have made more than a billion dollars in a year.
turns.response: That is a lot of money! I hope it goes to a good cause.
